{"key":"processedPost-6593173","value":{"id":6593173,"first":6592688,"last":6593173,"when":1172076047,"utime":"02/21/07 06:40 PM","content":"Get rid of the pumps, bubblers, standing water, and the ultrasonic.<br /><br />4\" of damp perlite will maintain proper humidity even with dozens or more holes drilled into the tub for FAE.  In mushroom growing, low tek works better than all the bells and whistles that a bill gates could afford to use.  As agar said, you want as close to 100% humidity as you can get.  You don't want it raining on your cakes.<br /><br />In addition, 24/7 light will degrade your pinset, if it pins at all.  Hyphal knots form during the dark cycle, not the light cycle.<br />RR","title":"Re: Is this set up over kill?"}}